author: Jeremy Page
title: China’s Leaders to Approve Economic Blueprint
text:
BEIJING—China’s Communist Party this week is expected to approve an economic blueprint for scaling back the role of the state over the next five years, while offering clues about the leadership’s appetite for bold reform in the face of slowing growth.
